Fix broken include in upstream commit bae932d (mediatek: add support for
device zbt-z8103ax-c). The new device's shared dtsi tries to include
'mt7981b.dtsi' which doesn't exist (only 'mt7981.dtsi' exists in kernel
headers). Without this patch, MTK target build fails for ALL devices
because target/linux/install compiles every device's DTB.

Upstream fix pending; remove this patch once ImmortalWrt 24.10 fixes it.

--- a/target/linux/mediatek/dts/mt7981b-zbtlink-zbt-z8103ax.dtsi
+++ b/target/linux/mediatek/dts/mt7981b-zbtlink-zbt-z8103ax.dtsi
@@ -2,7 +2,7 @@
 
 /dts-v1/;
 
-#include "mt7981b.dtsi"
+#include "mt7981.dtsi"
 
 / {
 	aliases {
